quran[62]{c,v,t}:
  37,83,Indeed among those who followed his way was Abraham
  37,84,"Behold, he approached his Lord with a pure heart"
  37,85,"Behold, he said to his father and to his people, “What is it you worship"
  37,86,“Is it false gods instead of God that you desire
  37,87,“Then what is your idea about the Lord of the worlds?”
  37,88,Then he cast a glance at the stars
  37,89,"And he said, “I am indeed sick.”"
  37,90,"So they turned away from him, and departed"
  37,91,"Then he turned to their gods and said, “Will you not eat"
  37,92,“What is the matter with you that you do not speak?”
  37,93,"Then did he turn to them, striking them with the right hand"
  37,94,"Then they came with hurried steps, and faced him"
  37,95,"He said, “You worship that which you have carved"
  37,96,“But God has created you and that which you make.”
  37,97,"They said, “Build him a furnace, and throw him into the blazing fire.”"
  37,98,"They then sought another strategy against him, but We made them the ones most humiliated"
  37,99,"He said, “I will go to my Lord, He will surely guide me"
  37,100,"“O my Lord, grant me one from the righteous.”"
  37,101,So We gave him the good news of a child ready to sacrifice and forbear
  37,102,"Then when he reached the age of work he said, “O my son, I see in a vision that I offer you in sacrifice. Now tell me what you see?” The son said, “O my father, do as you are asked. You will find me, God willing, one practicing patience and constancy.”"
  37,103,"So when they both submitted their wills, and he laid him prostrate on his forehead"
  37,104,"We called out to him “O Abraham,”"
  37,105,“You have already fulfilled the vision.” Indeed We reward those who do right
  37,106,For this was a challenge
  37,107,And We ransomed him with a momentous sacrifice
  37,108,And We left this blessing for him among generations to come
  37,109,“Peace and salutation to Abraham.”
  37,110,Indeed We reward those who do right
  37,111,For he was one of our believing servants
  37,112,"And We gave him the good news of Isaac, a prophet, one of the righteous"
  37,113,"We blessed him and Isaac, but of their progeny are some who do right and some who do wrong, to their own souls"
  37,114,Again We bestowed Our favor on Moses and Aaron
  37,115,And We delivered them and their people from great calamity
  37,116,"And We helped them, so they overcame"
  37,117,And We gave them the Clear Books
  37,118,And We guided them to the straight way
  37,119,And We left this blessing for them among generations to come
  37,120,“Peace and salutation to Moses and Aaron.”
  37,121,So indeed We reward those who do right
  37,122,For they were two of our believing servants
  37,123,Elias was also among those sent by Us
  37,124,"Behold, he said to his people, “Will you not be conscious"
  37,125,“Will you call upon Baal and abandon the Best of Creators
  37,126,“Your Lord and the Lord of your ancestors?”
  37,127,"But they rejected him, and they will certainly be called up"
  37,128,Except the sincere and devoted servants of God
  37,129,And We left this blessing for him among generations to come
  37,130,“Peace be upon Elias.”
  37,131,Then indeed do We reward those who do right
  37,132,For he was one of our believing servants
  37,133,Lot was also among those sent by Us
  37,134,"Behold, We delivered him and all his adherents"
  37,135,Except an old woman who was among those who lagged behind
  37,136,Then We caused the rest to perish
  37,137,"Indeed you pass by their sites, by day–"
  37,138,And by night. Then will you not use reason
  37,139,Jonah was also among those sent by Us
  37,140,When he ran away to the ship fully stocked
  37,141,"He cast lots, and he was condemned"
  37,142,Then the fish swallowed him. He had done things worthy of blame
  37,143,Had it not been that he glorified God
  37,144,He would certainly have remained inside the fish until the Day of Resurrection